timing_enable_pulsed_latch(25.10)            timing_enable_pulsed_latch(25.10)

Name
       timing_enable_pulsed_latch

Syntax
        timing_enable_pulsed_latch

       {true | false}

       Default: true

       Enables pulse-latch analysis.

       When  set to true, the pulse-latch analysis mode provides several addi-
       tional pulse-clock specific constraint specifications and reporting ca-
       pabilities.

       When in pulse-latch mode, you can use the following  pulse  clock  con-
       straints:

              * set_pulse_clock_max_width

              * set_pulse_clock_min_width

              * set_pulse_clock_max_transition

              * set_pulse_clock_min_transition

       Additionally,  in this mode, the report_constraint command supports the
       following pulse clock check types:

              * pulse_clock_max_width

              * pulse_clock_min_width

              * pulse_clock_max_transition

              * pulse_clock_min_transition

       To set this global variable, use the set_global command.

